DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The macro stores the cursor position of the specified win-
       dow in y and x.

       The macro, if the specified window is a subwindow,  stores
       in y and x the coordinates of the window's origin relative
       to its parent window.  Otherwise, -1 is stored in y and x.

       The  macro  stores  the absolute screen coordinates of the
       specified window's origin in y and x.

       The macro stores the number of rows of the specified  win-
       dow in y and stores the window's number of columns in x.

